hat he started on that branch.\n    60→\n    61→---\n    62→\n    63→## 2026-03-16 ~08:29 MDT — Third Heartbeat\n    64→\n    65→**Status:** Everything's shiny, Cap'n. Third watch, same steady hum. She ain't changed a thing since last I checked.\n    66→\n    67→**Engine diagnostics:**\n    68→- All 188 tests pass (969ms test time, 4.35s total) — five test suites, all green\n    69→- Build (`tsc`) compiles clean — no type errors\n    70→- No CI runs, no open PRs, no beads issues\n    71→\n    72→**Working tree:**\n    73→Same four uncommitted files on `fix/stale-tests-and-a11y`. Third heartbeat finding them. The work is good — a11y fix in template.ts, three test files updated. Tests all pass with these changes.\n    74→\n    75→**Changes since last heartbeat:** None. No new commits, no new branches.\n    76→\n    77→**Same concerns still open (3rd heartbeat each):**\n    78→- ESLint config missing — the code style fuel filter still ain't connected\n    79→- Patch deps available — Remotion, nanoid, prettier, eslint\n    80→- `.servitor/` still untracked\n    81→\n    82→**Assessment:** Quiet ship, healthy engine. Three heartbeats now with the same uncommitted work sitting on this branch. Nothing's degrading — she's flying fine. But that branch work is ready to land whenever Lee comes back. I'm standing by. A mechanic who fidgets when the engine's running smooth is a mechanic looking for trouble she don't need.\n    83→\n    84→---\n    85→\n    86→## 2026-03-16 ~12:28 MDT — Fourth Heartbeat\n    87→\n    88→**Status:** Everything's shiny, Cap'n. Fourth watch. Same steady hum. She's runnin' like a dream.\n    89→\n    90→**Engine diagnostics:**\n    91→- All 188 tests pass (343ms) — five suites, all green\n    92→- Build (`tsc`) compiles clean — no type errors\n    93→- No CI runs, no open PRs, no beads issues\n    94→\n    95→**Working tree:**\n    96→Same four uncommitted files on `fix/stale-tests-and-a11y`. Fourth heartbeat finding them. The a11y fix in template.ts